      "content": "but that's the thing tho. if the only reality is pain, then why is the logical move to endure it? it feels like we're being forced to participate in something inherently broken. if nothing matters in the grand scheme, then the \"point\" of staying alive for the sake of feeling something is just... it's just more unnecessary friction. it's like trying to keep a fire burning in a hurricane. why is there this massive pressure to keep struggling when the end result is guaranteed to be zero anyway?",
